[A Young Girl stands before you, garbed in customary Sith Force Trainer Robes, her hood pulled back to reveal purple hair tied in a ponytail, she begins to speak as you lean closer]

"The Force shall free me."

[The Young girl smiles, yet you can feel she is saddened]

"I have walked away from the Sith and the Imperium. Things have indeed changed."

[Her smile falters, and she frowns]

"I was forced to choose, those who had saved me before I became a Darth, or those whom I was an instrument to. I chose those I consider friends."

[The Holocrons image shifts, sitting on the 'floor' of the device, staring up at the large caverns ceiling]

"I'm not sure. I was advised by a... Friend, to view all the different 'factions' the universe holds, I wish to be as wise as him when I grow with age. A teacher, if you would say."

"Only time will tell, only time will tell."

"I am afraid this is where the Holocron ends."

"Farewell, <FirstName>."
[The Holocron flickers, and turns off]

[The Sith tilts her head, strangely enough she smiles]

" I am Lyrael, once known as Darth Ranimus."

[She sits, crossing her legs, developing a pose as if meditating]

" I teach that hatred is not the only emotion that may drive a Sith. That the Code of the Sith does not force us to walk one path. Passion will free us, it will make us strong."

"Yet Passion does not only inspire hatred, it inspires other things such as Love which in itself, is a dangerous thing. As a Darth even I watch how close to the edge I tread, not allowing myself to be consumed like so many before me."

"My Master taught me well."

[She smiles again, a care-free expression]

"If you asked me if I stay true to the code, I would answer yes. However I use the same sword others use, in a different manner."

"Just because I do not seeth in my hatred or become a bitter hag, does not mean I do not mentally break people, or choke them."

"Remember this, The Loudest one in the room, is the weakest."

"Beware those who sit quietly with a smile, and listen."

"I had. . . Or have, if I am still living, an uncanny ability with Telekinesis. I became a Master of my own Mind and my greatest test of strength has been building the very place around you with it."

"I mean, you don't believe I found a hollowed out cavern, do you?"
[She Grins]

"However, by becoming a Master of the Force, and Telekinesis, I have never found use for a Saber and in many situations, I do not use one due to my lack of Perfecting the LightSaber."

[The Sith tilts her head, strangely enough she smiles]

"I am Lyrael, known as Darth Ranimus, once Apprentice of Darth Ahasver."

[The Sith Mistress frowns, a faint glimpse of sadness in her eyes]

"Darth Ahasver. . . Perhaps another time."

[She motions to the surroundings around you]

"This is the Nightflower Sanctuary, my personal home. It is the only place I deem safe from the universe."

[She grins]

"Everyone needs, or has, a place that they feel completely safe in."

[She sits, crossing her legs, developing a pose as if meditating]

[She Grins]

"However, by becoming a Master of the Force, and Telekinesis, I have never found use for a Saber and in many situations, I do not use one due to my lack of Perfecting the LightSaber."
"Ranimus, Something seems different, you have changed."
"Why? What drove you to do this?"
"You are a fool. The Sith is the only power." [Leave]
"I see, that was a good choice Ranimus. What shall you do now?"
"It sounds like a long and difficult road, Lady Ranimus."
"What- How did you know my Name!?"
"Goodbye."
"Who are you?"
"What do you teach?"
"You're not like other Sith, what is to say that you truly are one?"
"I will heed your words." [Leave]
"What were/are your abilities? What did you excel at?"
"Who are you?"
"Who is Darth Ahasver?"
"I see, Goodbye Darth Ranimus, Lyrael."
"What is this place?"
"Safe from the Universe?"
"That is true." [Leave]
"What can you teach me?"
"You're not like other Sith, what is to say that you truly are one?"
"I see, Thank you." [Leave]
"What were/are your abilities? What did you excel at?"
"I see, thank you for the information, Goodbye Darth Ranimus." [Leave]
